solution.p:
First, we use the Pythagorean theorem to find the hypotenuse, c.
        \begin{align*}
                c^2 \amp =6^2 + 8^2\\
                c^2 \amp = 536=84 = 100 \amp\amp \text{Take square roots.}\\
                c \amp =  \sqrt{100} = 10\\                 
                \end{align*}
    For the angle \theta, the opposite side is 8 inches long, and the adjacent side is 6 inches long, as shown in the figure.  Thus,
        \begin{align*}
                \text{sin}~ \theta \amp = \dfrac{\text{opposite}}{\text{hypotenuse}} = \frac{8}{10}~~  \text{or}~~ 0.8\\
                \text{cos}~ \theta \amp = \dfrac{\text{adjacent}}{\text{hypotenuse}} = \frac{6}{10} ~~ \text{or}~~ 0.6\\
                \text{tan}~ \theta \amp =  \dfrac{\text{opposite}}{\text{adjacent}}  = \frac{8}{6} ~~ \text{or}~~1.\overline{3}\\                 
                \end{align*}
